sistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes de Maulmont was born about 1140, in Saint-Priest-Bramefant, Puy-de-Dôme, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France. She married Guillaume IV de Mauzé in 1163, in Mauzé-sur-le-Mignon, Niort, Deux-Sèvres, Poitou-Charentes, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in Mauzé-sur-le-Mignon, Deux-Sèvres, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France."},"et":{"Abt 1140–":"umbes 1140–Surnud","1135–1199":"1135–1199","1164–Female":"1164–Surnud","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","Abt 1175":"umbes 1175","Abt 1140":"umbes 1140","1135":"1135","1199":"1199","1164":"1164","1175":"1175","1163":"1163","1140":"1140","Mauzé-sur-le-Mignon, Niort, Deux-Sèvres, Poitou-Charentes, France":"Mauzé-sur-le-Mignon, Niort, Deux-Sèvres, Poitou-Charentes, Prantsusmaa","Mauzé-sur-le-Mignon, Niort, Deux-Sèvres, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Mauzé-sur-le-Mignon, Deux-Sèvres, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa","Mauzé-sur-le-Mignon, Deux-Sèvres, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Mauzé-sur-le-Mignon, Deux-Sèvres, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa","Saint-Priest-Bramefant, Puy-de-Dôme, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Saint-Priest-Bramefant, Puy-de-Dôme, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"Abt 1140–":"noin 1140–Kuollut","1135–1199":"1135–1199","1164–Female":"1164–Kuollut","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","Abt 1175":"noin 1175","Abt 1140":"noin 1140","1135":"1135","1199":"1199","1164":"1164","1175":"1175","1163":"1163","1140":"1140","Mauzé-sur-le-Mignon, Niort, Deux-Sèvres, Poitou-Charentes, France":"Mauzé-sur-le-Mignon, Niort, Deux-Sèvres, Poitou-Charentes, Ranska","Mauzé-sur-le-Mignon, Niort, Deux-Sèvre